RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Marysville, WA, operates under a mayor-council form of government. The mayor is elected, and there are seven at-large city council members. The council members are elected for four-year terms, and one member is selected to serve as Council President. Jon Nehring has served as Mayor since August 2010 and was re-elected in 2023. The listed council members are based on the official city website and recent news.
